'''''Hunter Patrol''''' is a [[shoot 'em up]] written by Steve Lee for the [[Commodore 64]] and published by [[Mastertronic]] in 1985.<ref name="giantlist"/> The music was composed by [[Rob Hubbard]]. The game is similar in style to the Sega arcade game ''[[Buck Rogers: Planet of Zoom]]''.

==Gameplay==
Taking control of a WW2 airplane, the player attacks enemy installations on the ground whilst avoiding enemy planes and flak. Once a sufficient number of installations are destroyed, the level's main target appears. When this had been taken care of the player moves on to the next level with the rewards of a score bonus and an extra life.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Zzap64|issue=7|url=http://www.zzap64.co.uk/cgi-bin/displaypage.pl?issue=007&amp;page=052&amp;thumbstart=0&amp;magazine=zzap&amp;check=1}}</ref>

